This article is a transcript of a press briefing given by White House Press Secretary Jay Carney on December 13, 2012. Carney discusses the ongoing negotiations regarding the fiscal cliff, criticizing Republicans for not providing specific proposals for spending cuts and revenue increases. He also addresses the issue of the debt ceiling, stating that the President believes Congress should adopt Senator McConnell's proposal to avoid defaulting on the country's credit. Carney also mentions the President's position on the conflict in Syria and the recent missile launch by North Korea.